<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Well an Enchanter class can certainly solo, that's for sure. They're the bane of all other classes on the PvP servers because they're a good solo class. Any of the pet classes can solo well.<P>I'd put it in this order, from best to worst, for solo classes:<P>Best:<BR>All pet classes - Enchanter, Spiritmaster, Theurgist. Chanters have an awesome pet in that it casts spells (at later levels). High damage output - can probably kill a yellow before it even gets a hit in on you, but you'll have butt-time regenning your power. Theurgists have much more temporary pets, but they can cast a bunch of them. Theurgists are widely respected as an excellent soloing pet class.<P>Good:<P>Charmer classes - Minstrel, Sorcerer, Mentalist, Hunter. You can charm some pretty mean mobs out there, and they make soloing a breeze. Charm a caster some time, like a Sylvan Goblin Magician. If you play it right, they'll stand back and blast the mob while you tank it. Or if your a pure caster, you can both blast it to smithereens.<P>Only downside to charmer classes is you have to go find a pet of the appropriate type/level, and some hunting areas have none. Without a pet, soloing as a minstrel is pretty weak. I wouldn't go after a yellow without a pet, that's for sure. Same for Sorcerers.<P>Average:<P>Bow classes (except Hunter, above). Scouts and Rangers can solo pretty well. No heal though, so since they have to tank at least a little, they have more downtime.<P>Blaster Casters - hey, I just made that up!  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> Wizards, Eldritches and Runemasters can certainly put the stank down, but if anything goes wrong they've got a big problem. Multiple pulls, resists, misses with bolts can all land you in a hurt locker. Plus you're going to have a lot of downtime regenning power no matter what happens.<P>Hybrid tanks (Paladin): I haven't played a lot of these, but the Paladin I did play solo'd pretty well. He was a tough bugger too.<P>Pure tanks - These are probably the worst class if you want to solo a lot - they just can't avoid damage and they can't heal, and as a result, they can't avoid downtime.<P>Stealth classes - No heal, and practically no armor. And no pet. The only upside is you can kill mobs pretty quick - but if he brings a friend, you've got a problem.<P>I wouldn't really put any class in a "poor" category. I think pretty much every character can solo blues reliably.<P>Other than that, I don't have any experience in Wardens, Clerics or Druid-types.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
